Rating: 3
We enjoyed this soup very much. A few changes: rather than using canned beans, I soaked some dried beans overnight and cooked those, then used them as the recipe recommends for canned beans. I used my own turkey broth rather than chicken broth. I used more Parmesan rinds...maybe 3 or 4. I used finely chopped ham instead of prosciutto (had it on hand). In addition to the sage, I made a sage oil by blending and straining sage in olive oil. I used it to squiggle over the soup after it was ladled into bowls. Very pretty, and the left over oil was used in a salad dressing later. Think this recipe works fairly well as written, although it obviously is tolerant of tweaking to fit what is in your cabinet. The resulting soup is a little thinner than I expected, but that turned out just fine when we floated some crostini on it.

